      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening justified for titanium alloy under quasi-static loading; contact formulation captures rod-screw interface behavior.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity (Ti-6Al-4V: E = 114 GPa, σ_y = 880 MPa, tangent modulus = 1.1 GPa) selected based on published coupon data. Augmented Lagrange frictional contact (μ = 0.2) at rod-screw and screw-block interfaces. Model form consistent with literature precedents for spinal implant FEA."
