      "rationale": "CMM-measured screw and rod dimensions used directly in FEA geometry. Material properties from same hardware lot as test specimens. Boundary conditions (fixed base plate, axial-bending load application point) replicate F1717 fixture geometry within 0.1 mm. Equivalency confirmed by overlay of CAD and CMM point cloud (RMS deviation 0.018 mm)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI difference < 10% for all three outputs; validation metric E/uval < 1.96 for each QoI.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness: FEA 487 N/mm vs. experimental mean 501 N/mm (2.8% difference, E/uval = 0.61). Yield force: FEA 1243 N vs. experimental mean 1267 N (1.9% difference, E/uval = 0.44). Force at 40 mm: FEA 1891 N vs. experimental mean 1923 N (1.7% difference, E/uval = 0.38). All acceptance criteria met."
    },
    {
